{
  "texts": [
    "֒→ * Router (192.168.0.1): This router routes traffic between the private LAN and the internet.",
    "֒→ * Internet: This is the public network that allows the server to communicate with other servers and devices located outside of the organization's private network.",
    "֒→ ֒→ Server B: * WAN (10.0.0.0/24): This is the wide area network that connects the server to other servers and devices located in different geographic locations.",
    "֒→ * Router (10.0.0.1): This router routes traffic between the WAN and the private LAN.",
    "֒→ * Private LAN (192.168.0.0/24): This is the internal network that connects the client devices within the organization."
  ]
}